## Finding the frequency of each activity. Which activity's are the most popular?

library(forcats)

sumdata = data.frame(count=apply(ausActiv,2,sum))
sumdata$key=rownames(sumdata)

sumdata <-sumdata %>%
  mutate(percent = round((count / 1003),2))

sumdata <-sumdata %>% 
  mutate(percent_label = label_percent(accuracy = 1)(percent))

sumdata_sorted <- sumdata %>%
  mutate(activity = fct_reorder(key, count, .desc = TRUE))

ggplot(data=sumdata, aes(x = fct_reorder(key, count),  y=count, width = .6)) +
  geom_bar(colour="black", stat="identity", fill="darkblue")+
  geom_text(aes(label=percent_label), hjust=-0.3, size=2.3)+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), panel.border = element_blank(), panel.grid.major = element_blank(),panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  xlab("Activity")+
  ylab("Frequency")+
  ggtitle("Popularity of Each Activity")+
  coord_flip()

# For loop to find the average spendpppd for each activity 
data <- na.omit(data)
vector <- vector()
activity_vector <- colnames(ausActiv)

average_data <- data %>% select(activity_vector,spendpppd)
Note: Using an external vector in selections is ambiguous.
 Use `all_of(activity_vector)` instead of `activity_vector` to silence this message.
 See <https://tidyselect.r-lib.org/reference/faq-external-vector.html>.
This message is displayed once per session.
for (i in 1:(ncol(average_data)-1)){
{
    new <- average_data %>% 
      filter(average_data[,i] == 1)
    
    newmean <- (mean(new$spendpppd))
 
  vector <- append(vector, newmean)
}
  i + 1
}

mean(average_spendpppd$vector)

[1] 79.70178
average_spendpppd <- average_spendpppd %>% mutate(rounded = round(vector,2))

ggplot(data=average_spendpppd, aes(x = reorder(activity_vector, -vector), y= vector, width = .75))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity", color="black",fill="darkblue")+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "none", plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), panel.border = element_blank(), panel.grid.major = element_blank(),panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1.2, hjust=1.1))+
  xlab("Activity")+
  ylab("Average Dollars per Day")+
  ggtitle("Average Dollars spent per Day")+
  geom_text(aes(label=rounded), vjust=-0.3, size=2.2)

## Finding the frequency of each activity for those in the year differences. 
library(forcats)

sumdata = data.frame(count=apply(ausActiv,2,sum))
sumdata$key=rownames(sumdata)

sumdata <-sumdata %>%
  mutate(percent = round((count / 1003),2))

sumdata <-sumdata %>% 
  mutate(percent_label = label_percent(accuracy = 1)(percent))%>% 
  filter(key == "Skiing" |key == "Hiking" | key == "Museum" | key =="Spa" | key == "Relaxing" | key == "Shopping"| key == "Sightseeing")
sumdata

sumdata_sorted <- sumdata %>%
  mutate(activity = fct_reorder(key, count, .desc = TRUE))

ggplot(data=sumdata, aes(x = fct_reorder(key, count),  y=count, width = .6)) +
  geom_bar(colour="black", stat="identity", fill="lightsteelblue")+
  geom_text(aes(label=percent_label), hjust=-0.3, size=2.3)+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "none", axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1), plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), panel.border = element_blank(), panel.grid.major = element_blank(),panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  xlab("Activity")+
  ylab("Frequency")+
  ggtitle("Popularity of Each Activity")+
  coord_flip()

# Creating a new dataframe with each of the averages forthe year difference activities
average_spendpppd_year_dif_activities <- average_spendpppd %>% 
  filter(activity_vector == "Skiing" |activity_vector == "Hiking" | activity_vector == "Relaxing" | activity_vector == "Shopping"| activity_vector == "Sightseeing")
average_spendpppd_year_dif_activities <- average_spendpppd_year_dif_activities %>% mutate(rounded = round(vector,2))

ggplot(data=average_spendpppd_year_dif_activities, aes(x = reorder(activity_vector, vector), y= vector, width = .75))+
  geom_bar(stat="identity", color="black",fill="darkblue")+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "none",  plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(), panel.grid.major.y = element_line( size=.1, color="grey" ) )+
  xlab("Activity")+
  ylab("Average Dollars per Day")+
  ggtitle("Average Dollars Spent per Day")+
  geom_text(aes(label=rounded), vjust=2, size=4, colour="white")
